reviews.review_text: gen admission $5.00 - any takers? hell ya! great 71 GD, this copy sounds a bit cleaner than the other copy on the ark. thanks mr.Lai and everyone else involved.

The GRATEFUL DEAD April 6, 1971 at the Manhattan Center NYC, NY .
.
.
....Hi-Fi Stereo Soundboard, excellent mix.

24 songs. A couple of collectables here. I'm a Hog for you Baby, & Dire Wolf (electric).

Performance is about a 4 out of 5. 

I recommend adding this show to your 1971 GRATEFUL DEAD collection.

Get it while you can, get it while it's free, get it now or you'll be sorry.

Eat, Drink, be Merry and Listen to the GRATEFUL DEAD.

Thanks for the Love.

Best Midnight Hour Ever Leaving aside the delicious treats of "Hog For You Baby" and "Oh Boy", this show featured what has to be considered by discerning Dead-ophiles, the Finest "Midnight Hour" of all time!  Certainly from the Pigpen era at the very least; though I doubt Bobby ever matched its piercing intensity.  Pigpen was absolutely in top form, tossing out a drunken philosophical nugget, from 6:26 - 6:31, that I've taken as something of a life lesson:

"Ain't no way to get around it, over, through; you gotta get in it, you gotta DO."

 Meanwhile Jerry, Bobby and Billy were in crazy synch with Pigpen in that jame

Seriously, the nugget of grace and wisdom Pigpen dropped at 6:26 makes this the greatest Mignight Hour ever in my book!
